# Scratchpad: Ecommerce Website Development Steps

## Phase 1: Project Setup & Foundation
1. Initialize Next.js 15 app with TypeScripts
   ```bash
   npx create-next-app@latest ecommerce-app --typescript --tailwind --eslint --app --src-dir --import-alias "@/*"
   ```
2. Install core dependencies
   ```bash
   npm install @radix-ui/react-icons @radix-ui/react-slot class-variance-authority clsx tailwind-merge lucide-react zod zustand recharts resend @uploadthing/react prisma @prisma/client next-auth@beta @paystack/paystack
   npm install -D @types/node
   ```
3. Setup Shadcn/ui
   ```bash
   npx shadcn-ui@latest init
   npx shadcn-ui@latest add button card input label form dialog badge dropdown-menu sheet
   ```
4. Configure environment variables (.env.local)
5. Setup PostgreSQL database
6. Initialize Prisma
   ```bash
   npx prisma init
   ```

## Phase 2: Database Schema & Models
1. Design database schema for ecommerce
2. Create Prisma schema with models:
   - User/Customer
   - Product
   - Category
   - Order
   - OrderItem
   - Cart/CartItem
   - Address
   - Payment
3. Run database migration
   ```bash
   npx prisma migrate dev --name init
   ```
4. Generate Prisma client
   ```bash
   npx prisma generate
   ```

## Phase 3: Authentication & User Management
1. Setup NextAuth.js configuration
2. Configure authentication providers (email/password, OAuth options)
3. Create guest checkout functionality
4. Build auth pages (login, register, forgot password)
5. Implement session management
6. Create user profile management

